SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/15/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>1:21:00 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Need info for Eyepatch of P+Collar of S Quests</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Eyepatch of Plunder</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Talk to the lost pirate which can be found on the first island in Iceclad Ocean. Once you hail him, he will mention the map he drew a long time ago and how he lost all the various pieces to it. Tell him that &quot;I want to find the pieces&quot; and he will hand you the cover of the book. He will tell you that once you obtain all four parts, put them in the book and combine them. <br>
<br>
The first part of the map drops off the Dire Wolf Stalker in Iceclad Ocean, who roams near the dragon bridge. The second part of the map is dropped by Stormfeather, a named griffon who spawns in Iceclad Ocean. To obtain the third part of the map, head over to the Great Divide and locate the cave with Bloodmaw. Hand Bloodmaw four Tizmak Meats and he will despawn, now say to the gnome &quot;I want the map please&quot; and he will hand you the third piece. The fourth piece is dropped by Lodizal, a giant sea turtle who also lives in the Iceclad Ocean zone. <br>
<br>
Combine the four pieces of the map in the book and then hand it to the Lost Pirate. He will hand you back the Completed Iceclad Map. Now run over and hand your new map to Captain Nalat and you will receive the Eyepatch of Plunder.<br>
<br>
-----------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Collar of the Storm</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Talk with Lieutenant Krofer who can be found in the Wakening Land. Say to him &quot;I am prepared&quot;. He will give you a Letter for War, and will tell you to give it to Staff Sergeant Drioc who can be found within Kael Drakkal. Drioc will sign it and hand it back to you, saying that the troops are ready to move. Return the note to Krofer, and he will hand you yet another note, which he will tell you to give back to him after the battle. <br>
<br>
Four giants will spawn and will run over to the Sifaye camp [1750, -275]. Now issue the command, &quot;troop attack&quot; and the giants will charge into the Sifaye camp. High level Sifaye's will spawn to defend their camp, basically you are meant to lose. Now return to Krofer and hand him back the letter he gave you. He will hand you the Failure Report and tell you once again tell you to go and see Drioc. Hand Drioc the report and he will tell you to go and see his financier, and then hands you back the Failure Report. <br>
<br>
His finacier is Noble Helssen who can be found next to Wenglawks in the Noble's building. Give Helssen the failure notice and he will tell you that it was not your fault and that Drioc was to blame. He then will divulge that he seeks to not only control the wakening land but the very force of Growth itself, and he needs your help. He will hand you a Tablet inscribed with special runes and tell you to seek out Corudoth, a named sea turtle, in the Iceclad Ocean. <br>
<br>
Head off to Iceclad Ocean and hand Corudoth, who can be found under a chunk of ice [-6000, 6000 ]. Hand him the tablet, he will reward you with a Lock of Hair. He will tell you to travel to Thugadin where you will have to look for Petcas, who owns a small bar. You must kill him to obtain the Ancient Rusted Key. From here you will travel to the Tower of Frozen Shadow and locate Abrams [Incoherant Spirit on 6th Floor]. Kill the spirit to make Abrams spawn, and then hand him the Lock of Hair. You will be rewarded with the Arcanum. <br>
<br>
Now head back to Helssen and hand him the Arcanum and the Ancient Rusted Key and he will hand you a voucher. From here, there are three different rewards that you can receive, depending on who you hand the voucher to. Hand the voucher to Kellek to receive the Collar of the Storm, or to Wenglawks to obtain the Girdle of Reflection, or lastly hand him back the voucher and he will hand you the Helssen's Prismatic Trinket.<br>
